### ============================================
### CalcsLive Plug for Inventor - API Tests
### Use VS Code REST Client extension
### ============================================

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:8000/ HTTP/1.1

###

### Inventor Health Check
GET http://localhost:8000/inventor/health HTTP/1.1

###

### Get Document Info
GET http://localhost:8000/inventor/document HTTP/1.1

###

### ============================================
### PARAMETERS
### ============================================

### Get All User Parameters
GET http://localhost:8000/inventor/parameters HTTP/1.1

###

### ============================================
### MAPPING (Comment field)
### ============================================

### Set Parameter Mapping (POST required!)
### Maps Inventor parameter "HeadPulleyDia" to CalcsLive symbol "D"
POST http://localhost:8000/inventor/parameters/mapping HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "HeadPulleyDia",
    "symbol": "Dp",
    "note": "Head Pulley Dia"
}

###

### Set Mapping with Value Update
### Updates both the mapping AND the parameter value
POST http://localhost:8000/inventor/parameters/mapping HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "diameter",
    "symbol": "D",
    "note": "Cylinder diameter",
    "value": 100.0,
    "unit": "mm"
}

###

### Remove Mapping (symbol: null clears the mapping)
POST http://localhost:8000/inventor/parameters/mapping HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "diameter",
    "symbol": null,
    "note": null
}

###

### Delete Mapping (alternative method)
DELETE http://localhost:8000/inventor/parameters/mapping HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "diameter"
}

###

### ============================================
### CREATE PARAMETER
### ============================================

### Create ArticleId Text Parameter
POST http://localhost:8000/inventor/parameters/create HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "ArticleId",
    "value": "3MAV4GNFQ-3FU",
    "comment": "eg: 3MAV4GNFQ-3FU, taken from article url",
    "unit": "Text"
}

###

### Create Numeric Parameter (with unit)
POST http://localhost:8000/inventor/parameters/create HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "SafetyFactor",
    "value": "1.5",
    "comment": "Design safety factor",
    "unit": "ul"
}

###

### ============================================
### UNIT CONVERSION
### ============================================

### Convert mm to inches
POST http://localhost:8000/inventor/convert HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "value": 609.6,
    "fromUnit": "mm",
    "toUnit": "in"
}

###

### Convert kg to lb
POST http://localhost:8000/inventor/convert HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "value": 100,
    "fromUnit": "kg",
    "toUnit": "lb"
}

###

### Convert temperature (C to F)
POST http://localhost:8000/inventor/convert HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "value": 100,
    "fromUnit": "C",
    "toUnit": "F"
}

###